added.title: Egg Hunt
added.description: Robin still regrets not being able to find an Easter egg when he was a kid, so the Titans head to Gotham to solve this mystery.

added.title: Kryponite
added.description: When Robin explains that knowing your weakness makes you a better superhero, Starfire journeys to find hers.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: As the other Titans engage in an all out thumb wrestling war, Starfire tries to broker peace.

added.title: Toddler Titans...Yay!
added.description: Control Freak thinks the Titans' humor is too juvenile for their time-slot, so he ages them down to a preschool show.

added.title: Easter Creeps
added.description: It's Easter and the Tooth Fairy is trying to take over the holiday.

added.title: The Stink
added.description: Gumball decides to put Mr. Small's eco-friendly principles to the test but it doesn't quite go as planned. Mr. Small disappears after deciding to leave the modern world behind. But on the plus side they discover that the Great Stink-Ape of Elmore Woods is definitely not extinct.

added.title: The Awareness
added.description: Gumball tries to convince Leslie he's an expert on all things plant-related. However, when Leslie realizes Gumball hasn't got a clue what he's talking about, he decides to call his bluff. An escalation of dangerous dares and stunts ensue as they try to out-plant each other.

added.title: The Slip
added.description: Richard doesn't answer the door in time and the jobsworth delivery guy will not let him have his package. His options are to pick his package up at the depot or pay for a redelivery. Richard doesn't like the sound of either option, so a battle of wills begins that can only end in the destruction of one or both of them.

added.title: The Drama
added.description: Everyone assumes Darwin and Carrie's relationship is doomed as they're so different. That is, everyone except Darwin and Carrie. When Carrie's cool ghostly ex-boyfriend turns up, Gumball decides to get Darwin to confront what's really going on.

added.title: The Buddy
added.description: Anais and school psycho Jamie are accused of the same techno-crime. They are forced to team up to discover the real culprit in order to prove their innocence. After solving the case, they realize that they have more in common than they thought...

added.title: Follow Your Dreams
added.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion are faced with a philosophical question: Are they truly doing good deeds for the good of other people or is it all just for them?

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: In order to appear on a successful kids show, Nom Nom must successfully complete anger management, with Grizz as his partner.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Cellie
added.description: Fed up with sharing, Panda forbids his brothers from using his cellphone any longer. But when the brothers get their own super advanced smartphones, Panda starts to succumb to crippling jealousy.

added.title: Chicken and Waffles
added.description: Panda needs to meet his brothers at the most exclusive restaurant in town. But when he loses his contacts lenses and can't see, Panda needs Charlie's help to get him into the city.

added.title: Together Alone
added.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: Are You My Dad?
added.description: People are disappearing from Beach City, and Steven tries to solve the mystery.

added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Web Weirdos
added.description: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: Hug Wolf
added.description: After an encounter with a Hug Wolf, Finn goes through a Jekyll and Hyde-like transformation becoming a hug-wolf himself!

added.title: Return to the Nightosphere
added.description: Marceline's dad banishes Finn and Jake to the Nightosphere, and it stinks. Literally.

added.title: Daddy's Little Monster
added.description: Finn and Jake return to the Nightosphere to rescue Marceline and get to the bottom of what's making her act so crazy.

added.title: Trailer Trashed
added.description: Muscle Man's trailer fails a health inspection and he wants to keep it at all costs.

added.title: Meteor Moves
added.description: Mordecai wants to finally kiss Margaret at a meteor shower.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: The Last Laserdisc Player
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and HFG want to get a laserdisc player so they can watch the director's cut of a cult classic.

added.title: Country Club
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to rescue the golf cart from a bunch of rich people at a country club.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea?: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: I See a Funny Cartoon in Your Future/Octi-Gone
added.description: I See a Funny Cartoon In Your Future: The girls have the rare task of fighting a medium who is committing petty thefts./Octi-gone: When Bubbles finds a single leg of Octi's, she sets out to find out who took her toy and what they want from her.

added.title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
added.description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

added.title: Nuthin' Special/Neighbor Hood
added.description: Nuthing Special: Frustrated with not knowing what her special power is, Buttercup hunts to discover what makes her special./Neighbor Hood: When everyone on Bubbles' favorite show loses their happy, Bubbles helps bring it back.

added.title: Hustlecup
added.description: When Buttercup loses the Professor's latest invention, she'll have to beat The Gangreen Gang at their own game to get it back.

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Tagalong
added.description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Chair
added.description: Unikitty finds an old, beatup recliner on the curb, but sees its inner beauty and brings it home to introduce to the gang! In a series of absurd and fun vignettes, we discover how a dirty, inanimate chair comes into each of their lives and changes them for the better. We soon learn that dear, sweet Chair was too good for this world.

added.title: Kickflip McPuppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn wants to impress his skater friends with his sweet skills, except he has none. Hoping to boost his confidence, Unikitty and the gang put on Dr. Fox's invisibility suits to secretly help him pull off impossible moves! But they do their job too well and "pro skater" Puppycorn is invited to showcase his skills in a dangerous stunt competition. How far will the gang go to help the pup live out his rad pipe dreams?

added.title: Super Amazing Raft Adventure
added.description: Unikitty and Hawkodile are "lost at sea", stranded on a raft together. Hawkodile sees this as an opportunity to show Unikitty that he's prepared for anything with his expertly-honed survival skills, but to his shock, all of his plans keep falling apart, while Unikitty's silly "it'll all work out, let's have fun" approach is somehow working great! Will Hawkodile manage to let go of his overpreparedness to save them both, or will Unikitty whimsical fun be their doom?

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Brawl Bot
added.description: Dr. Fox is proud to unveil her new ultimate combat machine and take it into an underground scientist fighting ring. But Hawkodile's jealous of Dr. Fox's fighting bot that's supposedly a better puncher than him and declares he can beat anything it can. To prove his point, he dresses up in spare robot parts and enters himself secretly in the bot battle. With Unikitty as his fighting coach, can Hawkodile survive the tourney, prove he's tougher than a machine, and avoid the scrap yard?

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise.

added.title: The Big Game
added.description: Chad takes Clarence to his first big game! Clarence takes it all in - the crack of the bat, the touchdown dances, the slam-dunks and of course, hotdogs and popcorn! But will Clarence get to fulfill his dream of meeting Aberdale's beloved mascot?

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: The Bike Ride
added.description: Pizza Steve desperately tries to prevent the gang from finding out his shameful secret.

added.title: Mr. Gus Moves Out
added.description: When a fed-up Mr. Gus moves out of the RV, Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve work together to get him back.

added.title: Hiccup Havok
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't get rid of the hiccups.

added.title: MacGuffin
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and a kid embark on a dangerous jungle adventure in search of a legendary MacGuffin.
